<item>
            <title>[TEXT-171] StringLookupFactory.addDefaultStringLookups(Map&lt;String, StringLookup&gt;) does not convert keys to lower case</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TEXT-171</link>
                <project id="12318221" key="TEXT">Commons Text</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Internally, the class &lt;tt&gt;org.apache.commons.text.lookup.InterpolatorStringLookup&lt;/tt&gt; normalizes its string lookup map with lower-case keys. The goal probably&#160;to make keys cases insensitive so you can say &quot;${env:USER}&quot; or &quot;${ENV:USER}&quot; or &quot;${Env:USER}&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The method &lt;tt&gt;org.apache.commons.text.lookup.StringLookupFactory.addDefaultStringLookups(Map&amp;lt;String, StringLookup&amp;gt;)&lt;/tt&gt; does not convert keys to lower case before adding entries to the string lookup map such that string look ups are not found when resolving variables.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This means that string lookup keys like &quot;resourceBundle&quot; that are &lt;em&gt;mixed&lt;/em&gt; case strings are not found and therefore not applied.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The list of keys that are not applied is:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;base64Decoder&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;base64Encoder&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;resourceBundle&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;urlDecoder&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;urlEncoder&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
